Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add potatoes, and cook until tender, about 25 minutes; drain. Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Stir in green onions, and cook until tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Mix green onions, horseradish, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese, milk, pepper and salt with potatoes. Mash together with a potato masher.